        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Introducing J. Alexander, a teacher.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p>New Orleans Nov 24th 1821</p>
<p>_______ <persName>Austin Esqr</persName>.</p>

<p>Dear Sir I take the liberty of recommending <persName>Mr J Alexander</persName> to
you as a useful man; I have been acquainted with him for some
years past, and belive him to be an honest gentleman: as a <persName>teacher</persName>
he had charge of an <placeName>academy in Georgia</placeName> in which capacity he 
discharged his duty much to the satisfaction of his <persName>employes </persName>etc&#8212;any
friendship exhibited to Sd <persName>Alexander</persName> will be thankfully 
acknowledged by your Hunble Sevt and respective friend</p>

<p><persName>Y M Daniel</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed:] ------&#8212; <persName>Austin Esqr</persName> Present</p>


        </div1>
    </body>
